1
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:34,583
[KAMIJO] Not long after
tranquility had been restored

2
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:37,416
to Misaka's life,
darkness returned.

3
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,458
This time, darkness
has taken the form of

4
00:00:39,541 --> 00:00:41,750
a shadowy organization
jostling for control

5
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:44,833
of Tree Diagram's wreckage.

6
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:47,083
And now Kuroko Shirai has
caught a glimpse of Misaka

7
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:49,166
as she wages her
lone, secret battle.

8
00:00:50,958 --> 00:01:00,958
♪ [Opening Song] ♪

9
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:32,833
Wait.

10
00:02:32,916 --> 00:02:35,625
[MIKOTO] Are there
any civilians in here?

11
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:37,333
[sighs]

12
00:02:48,416 --> 00:02:53,083
[MUSUJIME struggling]

13
00:02:53,166 --> 00:02:56,125
To your detriment you
underestimated me.

14
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:58,458
You assumed that I
wouldn't teleport myself.

15
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:02,958
I can do it anytime.

16
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,875
Provided I'm motivated enough.

17
00:03:04,958 --> 00:03:06,500
As long as the
goal's important,

18
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:08,916
the trauma isn't too bad.

19
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,041
[gasping in pain]

20
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:17,208
[KUROKO] I'm not sure you truly
understand how trauma functions.

21
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:19,833
It's not that easily
overcome, I'm afraid.

22
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:22,166
[KUROKO] Two years ago you
were seriously injured in

23
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,500
the process of
teleporting your own body.

24
00:03:24,583 --> 00:03:27,500
If I had to guess, you
most likely miscalculated

25
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:29,875
your coordinates and ran
into a wall or something.

26
00:03:29,958 --> 00:03:32,750
[KUROKO] And what a pathetic
sight that must have been!

27
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:38,041
[KUROKO] I'm sure
it hurts a lot,

28
00:03:38,125 --> 00:03:39,291
but there's no reason to panic.

29
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:41,791
I made certain to
avoid anything vital.

30
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:44,250
See, all I wanted to
do was to pay you back

31
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,500
for the injuries
you gave me earlier.

32
00:03:46,583 --> 00:03:48,250
Here is some styptic gel.

33
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,708
It's quite effective,
go ahead and try it.

34
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,791
[KUROKO] Now. I would like
to see you writhing in pain

35
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:57,333
on the cold floor while
you treat your own injuries.

36
00:03:57,416 --> 00:04:00,333
You do that, and I think we
can actually call things even.

37
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:01,958
[MUSUJIME chuckles]

38
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:03,708
You are quite
concerned about the fate

39
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,750
of Tokiwadai's
Ace, aren't you?

40
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:09,291
But really, what is it you're
trying so hard to protect?

41
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:11,291
Dear, sweet
Railgun's delusions?

42
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,458
The sentimental,
selfish, fantasy world

43
00:04:13,541 --> 00:04:15,166
that only she can see?

44
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:18,666
[KUROKO] That's exactly
what I want to protect.

45
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,083
However selfish
she might be sometimes,

46
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:23,833
what Sissy wants is
something truly good.

47
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:26,083
A world where you and I wouldn't
have to fight like this;

48
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,000
that's what she's working for!

49
00:04:28,916 --> 00:04:31,583
[KUROKO] Don't you get it?
All she needs is a single coin

50
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:34,291
and she could blow either
of us up where we stand.

51
00:04:34,375 --> 00:04:36,333
But even with all that
power at her fingertips,

52
00:04:36,416 --> 00:04:37,916
she holds back
because she honestly

53
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,583
believes the world
would be a better place

54
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,625
without so much violence.

55
00:04:41,708 --> 00:04:43,916
So you better
believe I find that to be

56
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,833
a future worth fighting for?

57
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,833
[KUROKO] And now I'm telling
you, in no uncertain terms,

58
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:50,125
to leave her alone.

59
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:52,208
Do you understand me, Musujime?

60
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:54,958
I want you to leave
Sissy and her dreams alone.

61
00:04:55,041 --> 00:04:57,166
[MUSUJIME] Is that so? And
what if I don't give a damn

62
00:04:57,250 --> 00:05:00,791
what you want? What are
you going to do about it?

63
00:05:04,541 --> 00:05:06,041
[plate breaks]

64
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:15,125
[KUROKO] I won't fall
for the same trick twice.

65
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:18,708
[thud]

66
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,791
Ahhh!

67
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:36,833
[KUROKO] I can't teleport!

68
00:05:41,416 --> 00:05:44,833
[crash]

69
00:05:51,375 --> 00:05:52,916
[MUSUJIME] What's the matter?
Were you in so much pain

70
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,250
you weren't able to teleport?

71
00:05:57,333 --> 00:06:00,916
[MUSUJIME] Here let me
tell you a little story.

72
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,541
Once upon a time in
a place not so far away,

73
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:05,875
there was an organization
interested in a powerful esper.

74
00:06:09,208 --> 00:06:10,958
[MUSUJIME] The organization's
leaders thought about

75
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,916
how strong they would
be if they had more espers

76
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,625
like her under their control,

77
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:17,708
and so they decided
to manufacture clones.

78
00:06:17,791 --> 00:06:20,208
[MUSUJIME] Unfortunately,
things didn't go as planned.

79
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:23,041
They wound up with a whole
bunch of near-useless sheep.

80
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:25,500
Colossal failures,
every last one of them.

81
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:28,291
Nowhere near as strong
as the Original esper.

82
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:33,083
[MISAKA 10032] "Okay then.
Shall we organize all of

83
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:35,291
the information we
have gathered so far?"

84
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:38,083
asks Misaka 10032
over the Network

85
00:06:38,166 --> 00:06:41,541
to an unspecified
number of units.

86
00:06:41,625 --> 00:06:43,083
"Currently, there
is a single Remnant

87
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:45,125
that can reestablish
Tree Diagram.

88
00:06:45,208 --> 00:06:47,166
[MISAKA 10032] It is
somewhere in Academy City."

89
00:06:47,250 --> 00:06:49,083
"The name of the organization
that is after it

90
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:50,750
is the Science Society.

91
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:53,541
There is no question
about that, correct?"

92
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:56,000
Misaka 10032 asks,

93
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:59,958
seeking to confirm
current information.

94
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:01,625
[MISAKA 10044] "Information
confirmed," replies

95
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:05,333
Misaka 10044,
without any doubt.

96
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:08,916
[MISAKA 10744] "However, 10032,
you of all units have suffered

97
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,291
the most severe damage.
You are still recuperating.

98
00:07:12,375 --> 00:07:16,583
Shouldn't you concentrate on
healing?" asks Misaka 10744,

99
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:19,458
expressing apprehension
with your involvement.

100
00:07:22,125 --> 00:07:25,416
"It doesn't matter,"
replies Misaka 10032

101
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:27,041
without hesitation.

102
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:29,916
[MISAKA 10032] "The
reintegration of Tree Diagram

103
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,375
is something that
must be stopped,

104
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:33,000
no matter the consequences."

105
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:36,291
says Misaka 10032,
remembering the faces of

106
00:07:36,375 --> 00:07:39,500
the boy and girl, thus
renewing her determination.

107
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:42,541
[MISAKA 14458] "Acknowledged.
We will leave it in your hands,

108
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:48,166
then," says Misaka 14458,
agreeing with 10032.

109
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,916
[MISAKA 19002] "We
appreciate your efforts,"

110
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,583
adds Misaka 19002,
with gratitude.

111
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:56,041
[LAST ORDER] "Misaka
thinks you are really great,"

112
00:07:56,125 --> 00:07:58,833
Misaka Misaka
says emphatically.

113
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,250
Misaka wishes that
she could help, too!

114
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:02,833
Misaka Misaka
really doesn't like

115
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:04,333
sitting around doing nothi--

116
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:06,000
[ACCELERATOR] Hey!

117
00:08:06,083 --> 00:08:08,333
[ACCELERATOR] Shut it, will ya?
What're you babbling about

118
00:08:08,416 --> 00:08:10,541
over there, you noisy brat?

119
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:14,666
[LAST ORDER] "Nothing at
all," says Misaka Misaka,

120
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,666
covering her mouth.

121
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:19,208
[sighs]

122
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,166
Tsk.

123
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:24,083
What do you think went wrong?

124
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,208
The clones are all genetically
identical to the Original,

125
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:27,708
and they have
undergone the exact same

126
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:29,833
ability development
as she has.

127
00:08:29,916 --> 00:08:31,500
[MUSUKIME] So how is it
possible, then, that they are

128
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:34,041
mere shadows of
her strength and power?

129
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:37,208
[MUSUJIME] Could it be that
there's something else involved

130
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:39,625
in the process besides
brain composition?

131
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:42,208
And, once we can identify
that, do you suppose

132
00:08:42,291 --> 00:08:45,333
non-humans will be able to
master abilities, as well?

133
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:48,958
[MUSUJIME] Something equal,
or even superior to people.

134
00:08:49,041 --> 00:08:52,375
The day they exist could be a
lot closer than you'd expect.

135
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:55,041
What in the world
are you talking about?

136
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:56,541
[KUROKO] You cannot
mean machines that

137
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:58,625
possess esper abilities!

138
00:08:59,291 --> 00:09:01,250
A machine is just a machine.

139
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,500
But machines can
make predictions.

140
00:09:03,583 --> 00:09:05,458
Suppose there was one that
could perfectly simulate

141
00:09:05,541 --> 00:09:08,625
any hypothetical situation
that was put to it.

142
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:10,916
[MUSUJIME] You could
ask it to assess

143
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,833
the possibility of anything.

144
00:09:12,916 --> 00:09:14,791
Like whether or not
abilities can be developed

145
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:18,000
outside of humankind,
for example.

146
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,833
Look at the animal kingdom.

147
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:22,000
Dolphins are called
the humans of the sea.

148
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:25,541
Ant societies are more orderly
and disciplined than ours.

149
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:27,166
[MUSUJIME] Surely
esper abilities are not

150
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:30,125
the sole province of men,
but if that's the case,

151
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,958
why haven't we seen
them anywhere else?

152
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:36,625
I want to know.
I have to find out.

153
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:38,958
[MUSUJIME] And that
is why I am doing this.

154
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:40,708
Why I want the Remnant,

155
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:44,125
so I can build a new Tree
Diagram and learn the answers.

156
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:47,041
[KAMIJO] Ee-yow!
I didn't do anything!

157
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:50,208
Why are you biting
me? Geez! Just let go!

158
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:52,458
Uh, I mean, "Pretty
please, let go, Index.

159
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:54,666
If you don't mind."

160
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,125
[INDEX] Ah!

161
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:00,625
[INDEX] You can be
really mean, you know that?

162
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:01,708
Eh?

163
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:04,708
I spent a lot of time and
effort trying to think up

164
00:10:04,791 --> 00:10:07,125
a personalized
tongue twister for you.

165
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:08,791
How did it go again?

166
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:11,500
"Toma traipses topless
through the town in a tutu?"

167
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:14,625
That doesn't exactly sound
complimentary, now, does it?

168
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,416
[KAMIJO] Uh, well,
what I meant was...

169
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,458
[doorbell rings]

170
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:21,916
[BOTH] Hmm?

171
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,458
[KAMIJO] Misaka? Hi.

172
00:10:27,541 --> 00:10:29,875
[MISAKA 10032]
"I have a favor to ask."

173
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:32,166
"Please," says
Misaka, staring you

174
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:35,583
directly in the eyes,
opening her heart up to you.

175
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:38,791
Misaka and Misaka's sisters'
lives are in danger.

176
00:10:38,875 --> 00:10:40,291
Will you come and help us?

177
00:10:40,375 --> 00:10:44,708
[running footsteps]

178
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,583
[MIKOTO] I won't allow it.

179
00:10:49,041 --> 00:10:51,500
[MIKOTO] Those
horrible experiments.

180
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:57,750
[MIKOTO] I can't let them
start up again, no matter what!

181
00:11:03,583 --> 00:11:06,500
[MIKOTO] "Extensive property
damage to an Area F restaurant,

182
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:09,125
in what appears to be a
skirmish between espers."

183
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:12,041
[MIKOTO] Eh! That idiot!

184
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:19,291
[breathing heavy]

185
00:11:19,375 --> 00:11:21,625
There you are... Zapper.

186
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:26,541
You were looking
for me? What for?

187
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:31,041
Why are you doing
this to me again?

188
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,916
[KAMIJO] Hey...

189
00:11:34,458 --> 00:11:36,791
Enough talk. Let's go.

190
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:44,125
[KUROKO] That is
why you collaborated

191
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:45,750
with an outside organization.

192
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,166
[MUSUJIME] Yes. Possessing
the Remnant is more than

193
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:52,916
half the battle, but I can't
restore the thing by myself.

194
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,041
So I needed an
outfit to partner with.

195
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:56,583
One that could
bring technical skill

196
00:11:56,666 --> 00:11:58,500
and intelligence to the table.

197
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:02,125
I'm curious, I want to know
something personal about you.

198
00:12:02,208 --> 00:12:03,416
[MUSUJIME] How did
it feel the first time

199
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,083
you used your ability?

200
00:12:05,166 --> 00:12:07,833
To be honest I
was actually afraid.

201
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:09,750
Possessing that kind
of power was scarier than

202
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,208
anything I'd ever experienced.

203
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:13,583
[chuckles]

204
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:15,375
Why does it have to be me?

205
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,708
Why does it have
to be a person at all?

206
00:12:17,791 --> 00:12:21,125
Are humans really the best
candidates to possess abilities?

207
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:23,125
[MUSUJIME] The members of the
organizations I've partnered

208
00:12:23,208 --> 00:12:25,750
with have the same
concerns and hesitations.

209
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:28,625
You see, they curse
their own abilities.

210
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:30,916
And like me, they've
been seeking answers.

211
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,500
We're all working together
for a common cause.

212
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:36,166
[MUSUJIME] That's why they were
willing to act as my shield.

213
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:38,375
You know what I'm
talking about, right?

214
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:40,958
That sick feeling you got
when you used your ability

215
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:43,166
and ended up
hurting somebody.

216
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:45,000
You aren't alone in that.

217
00:12:45,083 --> 00:12:47,541
In fact, I suspect
that we're a lot alike.

218
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:49,500
So, what do you say then?

219
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:52,041
Would you like to work together
with me to find the truth?

220
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:53,416
We'd love to have you.

221
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:56,583
You could be part of
something truly revolutionary.

222
00:12:58,083 --> 00:13:00,083
[KUROKO] Sorry, I'll
have to decline.

223
00:13:00,166 --> 00:13:02,333
Did you really think that
was going to win me over?

224
00:13:02,416 --> 00:13:04,416
A self-pitying,
self-involved monologue

225
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,208
and a lame
attempt at bonding?

226
00:13:06,291 --> 00:13:07,750
All you've managed
to prove so far

227
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:09,625
is that you like
to hear yourself talk.

228
00:13:09,708 --> 00:13:12,208
Don't you understand?
The powers that we espers

229
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:15,083
possess make us something
akin to mutant monsters.

230
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,166
These abilities
are too dangerous.

231
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:17,416
Oh, don't be absurd!

232
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:20,000
Abilities are abilities;
neither good nor evil.

233
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:22,541
How the power is used
depends on the person.

234
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:24,416
[KUROKO] How foolish do
you need to be not to have

235
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,500
realized something so obvious?

236
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:30,916
[KUROKO] You are
afraid of your power

237
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,625
because you don't
want it to hurt others?

238
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:36,833
You have so totally
missed the point.

239
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,291
[KUROKO] Whether
you have power or not,

240
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:42,208
nothing is going to change
the fact that you, Musujime,

241
